- The integer array parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The integer result is the number in the integer array `nums` with the value closest to 0.
- If there are multiple numbers with the same closest distance to 0, the number with the largest value is returned.
- The length of the integer array `nums` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 1000.
- All values in the integer array `nums` are greater than or equal to -100000 and are less than or equal to 100000.